{"title":"Candle of invocation","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Candle_of_invocation","type":"markdown","data":"| (           |                                  |\n| ----------- | -------------------------------- |\n| Name        | Candle of invocation             |\n| Appearance  | runed candle                     |\n| Base price  | 50 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\") |\n| Weight      | [2](/wiki/Weight \"Weight\")       |\n| Material    | [wax](/wiki/Wax \"Wax\")           |\n| Monster use | *Will not be used by monsters.*  |\n\nA **candle of invocation** is a type of [tool](/wiki/Tool \"Tool\") that appears in [dNetHack](/wiki/DNetHack \"DNetHack\") and [notdNetHack](/wiki/NotdNetHack \"NotdNetHack\"). It is made of [wax](/wiki/Wax \"Wax\") and appears as a **runed candle** when [unidentified](/wiki/Identification \"Identification\").\n\n## Generation\n\nIn addition to random generation, general [shops](/wiki/Shop \"Shop\"), lighting shops and hardware stores can sell candles of invocation.\n\nA candle of invocation will generate on the altar within the [Valley of the Dead](/wiki/Valley_of_the_Dead \"Valley of the Dead\") if the [ring of wishes](/wiki/Ring_of_wishes \"Ring of wishes\") generated at the [Castle](/wiki/Castle_\\(dNetHack\\) \"Castle (dNetHack)\") only has one charge.\n\n## Description\n\n[Applying](/wiki/Apply \"Apply\") a non-cursed candle of invocation will [light it](/wiki/Light_source \"Light source\") - a cursed candle cannot be lit, but will not be consumed if attempting to light it. A lit candle of invocation will never burn out, and [invoking](/wiki/Invoking \"Invoking\") the lit candle will allow the character to summon an extraplanar being from a set of menus, which consumes the candle afterward:\n\n- A [djinni](/wiki/Djinni \"Djinni\") can be summoned, which will immediately grant a [wish](/wiki/Wish \"Wish\") to the summoner.\n- An angel, demon, [fey](/wiki/Fey \"Fey\"), or [primordial](/wiki/Primordial \"Primordial\") can be summoned as a [tame](/wiki/Tame \"Tame\") servant.\n- A **hostile** demon lord can be summoned, with the demon lord being selected by input from another menu.\n\n## Strategy\n\nA lit candle of invocation is a useful light source for [Gehennom](/wiki/Gehennom \"Gehennom\") and other dark levels, but its primary use for a majority of characters is to summon a monster and either wish for a particular item or else shoot for a demon lord's particular equipment. For a character seeking to summon a pet, see the [pet](/wiki/Pet \"Pet\") article for suggestions.\n\n[![This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.](/images/5/5d/Nh343var-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Candle of invocation - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Candle_of_invocation\",\"wgTitle\":\"Candle of invocation\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":167217,\"wgRevisionId\":167217,\"wgArticleId\":36472,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Variant-343 articles\",\"DNetHack tools\",\"NotdNetHack tools\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Candle_of_invocation\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":36472,\"wgRequestId\":\"cb70b51e38b4abdfcf177c46\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"ready\",\"user.tokens\":\"loading\",\"mediawiki.legacy.shared\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.skinning.interface\":\"ready\",\"skins.vector.styles\":\"ready\"});mw.loader.implement(\"user.tokens@0tffind\",function($,jQuery,require,module){/*@nomin*/mw.user.tokens.set({\"editToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"patrolToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"watchToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"csrfToken\":\"+\\\\\"});\n});RLPAGEMODULES=[\"site\",\"mediawiki.page.startup\",\"mediawiki.user\",\"mediawiki.page.ready\",\"mediawiki.searchSuggest\",\"skins.vector.js\"];mw.loader.load(RLPAGEMODULES);});</script>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmediawiki.skinning.interface%7Cskins.vector.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<script async=\"\" src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=startup&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector\"></script>\n<meta name=\"ResourceLoaderDynamicStyles\" content=\"\"/>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=site.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<meta name=\"generator\" content=\"MediaWiki 1.32.5\"/>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"A candle of invocation is a type of tool that appears in dNetHack and notdNetHack. It is made of wax and appears as a runed candle when unidentified.\"/>\n<link rel=\"image_src\" href=\"/images/6/65/Nethackwiki-logo.png\"/>\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/images/6/64/Favicon.ico\"/>\n<link rel=\"search\" type=\"application/opensearchdescription+xml\" href=\"/opensearch_desc.php\" title=\"NetHackWiki\"/>\n<link rel=\"EditURI\" type=\"application/rsd+xml\" href=\"https://nethackwiki.com/api.php?action=rsd\"/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"/wiki/Candle_of_invocation\"/>\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=html5shiv&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector&amp;sync=1\"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class=\"mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Candle_of_invocation rootpage-Candle_of_invocation skin-vector action-view\">\t\t<div id=\"mw-page-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Candle of invocation</h1>\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From NetHackWiki</div>\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#p-search\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<table class=\"prettytable\" style=\"margin: 0;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><span class=\"nhsym clr-orange\">(</span>\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Name\n</th>\n<td>Candle of invocation\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Appearance\n</th>\n<td>runed candle\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Base price\n</th>\n<td>50 <a href=\"/wiki/Zorkmid\" title=\"Zorkmid\">zm</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Weight\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Weight\" title=\"Weight\">2</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Material\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Wax\" title=\"Wax\">wax</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Monster use\n</th>\n<td><small><i>Will not be used by monsters.</i></small>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n</div>\n<p>A <b>candle of invocation</b> is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Tool\" title=\"Tool\">tool</a> that appears in <a href=\"/wiki/DNetHack\" title=\"DNetHack\">dNetHack</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/NotdNetHack\" title=\"NotdNetHack\">notdNetHack</a>. It is made of <a href=\"/wiki/Wax\" title=\"Wax\">wax</a> and appears as a <b>runed candle</b> when <a href=\"/wiki/Identification\" title=\"Identification\">unidentified</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Generation\">Generation</span></h2>\n<p>In addition to random generation, general <a href=\"/wiki/Shop\" title=\"Shop\">shops</a>, lighting shops and hardware stores can sell candles of invocation.\n</p><p>A candle of invocation will generate on the altar within the <a href=\"/wiki/Valley_of_the_Dead\" title=\"Valley of the Dead\">Valley of the Dead</a> if the <a href=\"/wiki/Ring_of_wishes\" title=\"Ring of wishes\">ring of wishes</a> generated at the <a href=\"/wiki/Castle_(dNetHack)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Castle (dNetHack)\">Castle</a> only has one charge.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Apply\" title=\"Apply\">Applying</a> a non-cursed candle of invocation will <a href=\"/wiki/Light_source\" title=\"Light source\">light it</a> - a cursed candle cannot be lit, but will not be consumed if attempting to light it. A lit candle of invocation will never burn out, and <a href=\"/wiki/Invoking\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Invoking\">invoking</a> the lit candle will allow the character to summon an extraplanar being from a set of menus, which consumes the candle afterward:\n</p>\n<ul><li>A <a href=\"/wiki/Djinni\" title=\"Djinni\">djinni</a> can be summoned, which will immediately grant a <a href=\"/wiki/Wish\" title=\"Wish\">wish</a> to the summoner.</li>\n<li>An angel, demon, <a href=\"/wiki/Fey\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fey\">fey</a>, or <a href=\"/wiki/Primordial\" title=\"Primordial\">primordial</a> can be summoned as a <a href=\"/wiki/Tame\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tame\">tame</a> servant.</li>\n<li>A <b>hostile</b> demon lord can be summoned, with the demon lord being selected by input from another menu.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Strategy\">Strategy</span></h2>\n<p>A lit candle of invocation is a useful light source for <a href=\"/wiki/Gehennom\" title=\"Gehennom\">Gehennom</a> and other dark levels, but its primary use for a majority of characters is to summon a monster and either wish for a particular item or else shoot for a demon lord's particular equipment. For a character seeking to summon a pet, see the <a href=\"/wiki/Pet\" title=\"Pet\">pet</a> article for suggestions.\n</p>\n<div style=\"display:none; right:10px; padding-bottom: 17px\" class=\"metadata topicon nopopups\"><div style=\"margin-top: -10px\"><a href=\"/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version\" title=\"This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.\"><img alt=\"This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.\" src=\"/images/5/5d/Nh343var-icon.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240926182722\nCache expiry: 604800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.012 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.016 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 113/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 674/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 1671/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 303/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,m